INSERT INTO `learn` (`class`, `h3`, `p`, `id`, `related_posts`, `html`, `image_name`) VALUES
('fa-wallet', 'Crypto wallets & Crypto Exchanges', 'Learn about differences of crypto wallets.', 1, 'best', '    <br>\r\n    <h2>Crypto exchanges</h2>\r\n    <br>\r\n    <p>If you have crypto on exchanges, you don\'t own that money. You are paying company to hold your crypto, it\'s not yours. </p>\r\n    <br>\r\n    <li>Governments may have the authority to freeze or seize assets belonging to exchanges that operate within their jurisdiction.</li>\r\n    <li>You may be at risk of tax theft, asset forfeiture theft, and civil theft.</li>\r\n    <li>You may be at risk of exit theft.</li>\r\n    <li>You make job for black hat hackers easy</li>\r\n    <br>\r\n    <p>\r\n        Cryptocurrency security is a top concern for many investors, especially when it comes to protecting their digital \r\n        assets through the use of a crypto wallet. But with so many options available, it can be tough to determine which \r\n        wallets offer the highest level of security. In this article, we\'ll provide an overview of some of the most secure \r\n        crypto wallets currently on the market, as well as offer tips for selecting the safest option for your needs. \r\n        Remember, the ultimate security of your crypto wallet depends on how you manage it, so be sure to consider \r\n        all the factors that go into keeping your assets safe.\r\n    </p>\r\n\r\n    <p>\r\n        Storing crypto on exchanges, banks, or web wallets can be risky and can contribute to the centralization of the crypto \r\n        ecosystem. This can lead to increased security vulnerabilities and reduced decentralization of the network. Instead, \r\n        it is generally considered more secure to store your crypto in a personal wallet that you control, such as a hardware wallet.\r\n        This allows you to maintain control over your private keys, which are necessary to access \r\n        and use your crypto. By keeping your crypto in a personal wallet, you can help ensure the security of your \r\n        assets and contribute to the overall security and decentralization of the crypto network.\r\n    </p>\r\n\r\n    <p>\r\n        When you download a cryptocurrency wallet, you may be prompted to get your seed keys. \r\n        These keys are displayed on the screen for you to read. However, you should be aware that your phone may have been \r\n        exposed to malicious sites or apps, which could have infected your device with malware. Many people\'s devices \r\n        are infected with malware, and someone may be able to use a key logger to watch your activity through the \r\n        infected software. Therefore, it\'s important to be cautious when downloading mainstream wallets, as your screen may \r\n        be captured as soon as you download or run the wallet.\r\n    </p>\r\n    <br>\r\n    <h2>On a cryptocurrency exchange, you don\'t have control over your own digital assets.</h2>\r\n    <br>\r\n    <h3>Organizations such as Coinbase and Visa have implemented measures to block Russian citizens from accessing their services.</h3>\r\n    <br>\r\n    <p>Message from Coinbase:</p>\r\n    <b>â€žImportant: Action required by May 31, 2022 to avoid losing access to your Coinbase account. To comply with EU sanctions that prohibit Coinbase from providing crypto services to certain Russian customers, Coinbase will soon restrict your ability to access your account. Before May 31, 2022, you need to withdraw all funds from your account or provide us with specific documents to show you are not covered by these sanctions. After that date you risk your funds being frozen. Additional funds sent to your Coinbase account during this time period may also be frozen.</b>\r\n    <br>\r\n    <br>\r\n    <h2>Solution</h2>\r\n    <br>\r\n    <li>Use hardware wallets</li>\r\n    <li>Dont use Crypto Exchanges</li>\r\n    <li>Use seperate, clean device only for crypto</li>\r\n    <li>Don\'t use public WIFI</li>\r\n    <li>Change your password regularly</li>\r\n    <br>\r\n    <p>\r\n        The only current way to secure your crypto is to store it in a hardware wallet, I personally use both Trezor and Ledger\r\n        I suggest that you get ones without Bluetooth because the most time-consuming and difficult aspect of hacking a device\r\n        is often the information-gathering and planning stages. By reducing the attack surface device has, \r\n        you make it more difficult for attackers to gain access.\r\n    </p>\r\n\r\n    <p>\r\n        I use Trezor and Ledger hardware wallets because they provide an extra layer of security for my cryptocurrency. \r\n        When you first create a wallet on a hardware device, it generates a seed key, which is a list of \r\n        random words that are displayed on the device\'s screen. This ensures that no hacker can access the key, \r\n        as it is not stored on your smartphone or computer. It\'s important to write down the seed key and \r\n        store it in a secure, location, possibly in multiple pieces, to ensure the safety \r\n        of your crypto assets. Using a hardware wallet is a smart way to store cryptocurrency. Quite opposite of crypto exchanges.\r\n    </p>\r\n    <br>', '1.webp'),
('fa-medal', 'Best Privacy Coin', 'Privacy coins are undervalued in the cryptocurrency space.', 2, 'best', ' <h2>Monero</h2>\r\n    <br>\r\n    <p>\r\n        Monero is a popular privacy coin that allows users to conduct digital transactions privately and anonymously.\r\n        Unlike Bitcoin, which is often perceived as anonymous and untraceable, Monero actually has these features. \r\n    </p>\r\n\r\n    <p>\r\n        Bitcoin is no longer anonymous because individuals are linking their identities to their Bitcoin transactions through exchanges. \r\n        When a person uploads their identification to an exchange and uses it to purchase Bitcoin, their identity becomes permanently \r\n        associated with that specific coin.\r\n    </p>\r\n\r\n    <p>\r\n        Monero is not widely available on exchanges, which is where many normies typically \r\n        purchase their coins. Additionally, institutions tend to avoid Monero due to its potential association with \r\n        illegal activities and the risk of scrutiny from government agencies such as the IRS. There is significant \r\n        institutional resistance to Monero, and it has been banned in some locations and may be banned in others in the future. \r\n        The media often portrays Monero as being connected with terrorism and crime, similar to how Bitcoin was once perceived.\r\n    </p>\r\n\r\n    <p>\r\n        Monero was designed with technology that allows it to operate on the blockchain without revealing users\r\n        wallet addresses or transaction amounts. It also has a built-in mixer function, similar to those used for Bitcoin. \r\n        Monero\'s strong privacy features have attracted the attention of government agencies such as the IRS, which \r\n        has offered a $625,000 bounty for anyone who can develop a method for tracing Monero transactions.\r\n    </p>\r\n    <br>\r\n    <strong>\r\n        Despite this, Monero remains a highly secure and private cryptocurrency option, making it ideal for \r\n        users who want to protect their financial transactions from being monitored.\r\n    </strong>\r\n    <br>\r\n    <br>\r\n    <p>\r\n        An example of the privacy provided by the traditional banking system is the ability to transfer money to a \r\n        friend without revealing how much each person has. In contrast, using cryptocurrencies like BTC, ETH, \r\n        or others (excluding Monero) would allow both parties to see each other\'s balances, as well as the amount \r\n        of cryptocurrency being sent or received. This lack of privacy makes it unlikely that any cryptocurrency \r\n        will be able to replace fiat, unless it can offer better privacy protection than fiat. Monero addresses \r\n        this issue by providing stronger privacy features.\r\n    </p>\r\n    <p>I am a big fan of Monero because of its commitment to freedom and privacy. I believe it has a bright future and will do everything I can to support it</p>\r\n    <br>', '2.webp'),
