ed in the United Kingdom in 1919 to improve the lives of children.</p>\r\n            <strong><li>Mexico\'s Universidad de las AmÃ©ricas Puebla</li></strong> <p> - Commonly known as UDLAP, is a Mexican private university located in San AndrÃ©s Cholula, near Puebla.</p>\r\n            <strong><li>Famsa</li></strong> <p> - Retail company engaged in the purchase and sale of household appliances, electronic products, furniture, clothing and other consumer products in Mexico and United States.</p>\r\n            <strong><li>Naughty America</li></strong> <p> - Adult stuff, don\'t look it up if you are under 18!</p>\r\n            <strong><li>RE/MAX London</li></strong> <p> - Global estate agency network that spreads across over 115 countries on six continents.</p>\r\n            <strong><li>T-Mobile Poland</li></strong> <p> - Polish mobile phone network operator.</p>\r\n            <strong><li>CEX</li></strong> <p> - British second hand retail store specialising in technology, computing, video games, DVDs and technology repair.</p>\r\n            <strong><li>Vipernews</li></strong> <p> - Premium Usenet access (also known as newsgroups) for a reasonable price all year round.</p>\r\n        </div>', '3.webp'),
('fa-triangle-exclamation', 'Common Crypto Scams', 'Scams often involve financial gain, and this is also true in the world of cryptocurrency.', 4, 'scams', '<h2>It can be helpful to be aware of the various types of scams that exist in the world of cryptocurrency. Some common types of cryptocurrency scams include:</h2>\r\n    <br>\r\n    <br>\r\n    <ol>\r\n\r\n        <li><strong>NTF</strong></li>\r\n        <p>NFT projects may be created with the sole purpose of generating profit for the creators without offering any real value to collectors or users. These types of projects may be seen as \"cash grabs,\" as they are primarily focused on generating revenue without providing any significant value or utility.</p>\r\n        \r\n        <li><strong>Phishing scams</strong></li>\r\n        <p>These scams involve tricking individuals into giving away their personal and financial information, such as login credentials or private keys, through fake websites or emails that appear to be legitimate.</p>\r\n\r\n        <li><strong>Ponzi schemes</strong></li>\r\n        <p>These scams involve promising high returns on investment with little or no risk. They often rely on new investors to pay the returns of earlier investors, and eventually collapse when there are not enough new investors to sustain the scheme.</p>\r\n\r\n        <li><strong>Investment scams</strong></li>\r\n        <p>These scams involve convincing individuals to invest in fake or non-existent cryptocurrency projects, with the promise of high returns.</p>\r\n\r\n        <li><strong>Cloud mining scams</strong></li>\r\n        <p>These scams involve selling the idea of \"cloud mining,\" in which individuals can earn cryptocurrency by renting out the processing power of a remote server. However, these operations are often not legitimate and may not actually be mining cryptocurrency at all.</p>\r\n\r\n        <li><strong>Pump and dump schemes</strong></li>\r\n        <p>These scams involve artificially inflating the price of a cryptocurrency through coordinated buying, in order to sell it at a higher price to unsuspecting buyers.</p>\r\n\r\n        <li><strong>Ransomware scams</strong></li>\r\n        <p>These scams involve using malware to lock access to a device or system until a ransom is paid, often in cryptocurrency.</p>\r\n\r\n        <li><strong>ICO scams</strong></li>\r\n        <p>These scams involve fake initial coin offerings (ICOs), in which individuals are convinced to invest in a non-existent or fraudulent cryptocurrency project.</p>\r\n\r\n        <li><strong>Social media scams</strong></li>\r\n        <p>These scams involve using social media platforms to promote fake or fraudulent cryptocurrency projects, or to trick individuals into giving away their personal and financial information. </p>\r\n\r\n        <li><strong>Wallet scams</strong></li>\r\n        <p>These scams involve creating fake cryptocurrency wallet apps or websites, which may be used to steal individuals\' cryptocurrency assets.</p>\r\n\r\n        <li><strong>Escrow scams</strong></li>\r\n        <p>These scams involve using fake escrow services to facilitate fraudulent cryptocurrency transactions.</p>\r\n\r\n        <li><strong>Airdrop scams</strong></li>\r\n        <p>These scams involve fake airdrops, in which individuals are promised free cryptocurrency in exchange for their personal and financial information.</p>\r\n\r\n        <li><strong>Code injection scams</strong></li>\r\n        <p>These scams involve injecting malicious code into legitimate cryptocurrency projects, which may be used to steal users\' assets or personal information.</p>\r\n\r\n        <li><strong>Exchange scams</strong></li>\r\n        <p>These scams involve fake or unregulated cryptocurrency exchanges, which may be used to steal users\' assets or personal information.</p>\r\n\r\n        <li><strong>Trading bot scams</strong></li>\r\n        <p>These scams involve selling fake or non-functional trading bots, which are supposed to automate the buying and selling of cryptocurrency.</p>\r\n\r\n        <li><strong>Malware scams</strong></li>\r\n        <p>These scams involve using malware to infect devices and steal cryptocurrency assets or personal information.</p>\r\n\r\n    </ol>\r\n    <br>\r\n    <p>It is important to be cautious and to do thorough research before investing in any cryptocurrency project or offering. By being aware of these and other types of scams, you can help to protect yourself and your assets from potential fraudulent activity.</p>', '4.webp'),
('fa-question', 'What is the blockchain?', 'Blockchain - a tool with many purposes.', 5, 'whatis', '<h2>What is the blockchain?</h2>\r\n<br>\r\n<p>\r\n    Blockchain is a distributed ledger technology that consists of a growing chain of blocks, or records, that hold information about transactions that have occurred online. Each block contains data encoded in a chronological manner, and these blocks are linked together in a way that makes it difficult to alter the data contained within them. The information stored in a blockchain is decentralized, meaning it is not stored in a single location, but rather is distributed across a network of computers. This makes it secure and resistant to tampering. Blockchain technology is used in a variety of applications, including the creation and transfer of cryptocurrency, supply chain management, and secure record-keeping.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>What can be stored on blockchain?</h2>\r\n<br>\r\n<p>\r\n    The blockchain is a distributed database that allows for the storage of digital records, also known as blocks. These blocks can contain a variety of information, including financial transactions, contracts, identities, and other forms of data. Essentially, any type of information that can be represented in digital form can potentially be stored on the blockchain.\r\n</p>\r\n    \r\n<p>\r\n    One of the key characteristics of the blockchain is that it is decentralized, meaning that it is not controlled by any single entity or organization. Instead, it is maintained by a network of participating computers, also known as nodes, that validate and record transactions on the blockchain. This decentralized nature of the blockchain allows for the storage of information in a transparent and secure manner, as the data is replicated across the network and can only be modified with the consensus of the participating nodes.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n    In addition to storing various types of data, the blockchain can also be used to support smart contracts, which are self-executing contracts with the terms of the agreement between buyer and seller being directly written into lines of code. These contracts can be used to automate a variety of processes and transactions, including financial transactions, supply chain management, and more.\r\n</p>', '5.webp'),
('fa-landmark', 'Blockchain vs Banks', 'Blockchain eliminates the need for middlemen.', 6, 'blockchain', '<h2>What are the benefits of the blockchain?</h2>\r\n<br>\r\n\r\n<p>Crypto-currencies offer a number of benefits, including faster transfer speeds, lower transaction costs, reduced risk of manipulation by central governments, and global availability. </p>\r\n\r\n<br>\r\n<li>One of the key features of the blockchain is that it allows for decentralized ownership and control of digital assets.</li>\r\n<br>\r\n<li>Each participant in the network has a copy of the database, which ensures the immutability of the data.</li>\r\n<br>\r\n<li>The blockchain is accessible to anyone with an internet connection and can be integrated into various apps and websites.</li>\r\n<br>\r\n<li>The blockchain maintains a public record of all balances and transactions that is available to anyone, rather than being restricted to a single company\'s systems.</li>\r\n<br>\r\n<li>Blockchain technology provides a secure and cost-effective method of sending payments that eliminates the need for third-party verification and reduces processing times compared to traditional bank transfers.</li>\r\n<br>\r\n<li>Security: The decentralized nature of the blockchain and the use of cryptography to secure transactions make it a secure platform for storing and transferring digital assets. Traditional banking systems, on the other hand, are more vulnerable to attacks and fraud.</li>\r\n<br>\r\n<br>\r\n\r\n<p>The lengthy processing times for traditional bank transfers, which can take up to three days to settle, are due to the complex nature of the current financial infrastructure. Bank transfers often have to pass through a series of intermediaries, such as correspondent banks and custodial services, before reaching their destination. This process involves reconciling the balances of the two banks across a global financial system that involves a wide range of traders, funds, asset managers, and other entities. This can be a logistical challenge for banks, as well as a inconvenience for consumers. Blockchain technology offers an alternative by providing a more efficient and secure way to transfer funds directly between parties, bypassing the need for intermediaries and reducing processing times.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It is difficult to predict whether or not crypto-currencies will completely replace traditional banking systems in the future. While crypto-currencies offer a number of benefits, such as faster transfer speeds, lower transaction costs, and increased security, they also have their own set of challenges and limitations.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>For example, crypto-currencies are still not widely accepted as a form of payment, and their value can be volatile due to market fluctuations. In addition, the regulatory landscape for crypto-currencies is still evolving, and there is a lack of clarity around how they will be treated by governments and financial authorities in the long term.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Given these challenges, it is likely that traditional banking systems will continue to play a significant role in the global economy, even if crypto-currencies gain wider adoption. It is possible that the two systems may coexist and interact with each other in various ways, rather than one completely replacing the other.</p>\r\n<br>', '6.webp'),
('fa-question', 'What is an NFT?', 'NFTs gained popularity in 2020 and have continued to grow in popularity since then.', 7, 'whatis', '<p>NFT stands for non-fungible token, which is a digital item, such as a collectible avatar or a ticket, that is stored on the blockchain as a digital token. This token is unique and cannot be exchanged for an equal value like traditional fungible tokens, such as currency. For example, even if two NFTs have the same image, each token is unique and limited in number.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>The value of NFTs</h2>\r\n<br>\r\n<p>NFTs have a value that is determined by the market, based on supply and demand. They can be bought and sold in the same way as physical assets, and they can represent both digital and physical items, such as artwork or real estate. Some users see tokenizing real-world assets in this way as a way to make buying, selling, and trading them more efficient, as well as potentially reducing the risk of fraud. NFTs provide a secure and transparent way to own and trade unique digital items.</p>\r\n\r\n<br>\r\n<h2>How to create an NFT?</h2>\r\n<br>\r\n<p>To create an NFT, an artist or creator will first create a digital asset, such as a piece of art or a collectible. They will then use special software to create a unique digital token that represents ownership of that asset. This token is typically stored on a blockchain, such as Ethereum, which allows for the decentralized ownership and transfer of the asset.</p>\r\n<br>\r\n\r\n<h2>How do you buy NFTs?</h2>\r\n<p>To purchase an NFT, a buyer can use a cryptocurrency, such as Ether (ETH), to purchase the token from the creator or from a marketplace. Once the purchase is complete, the buyer becomes the owner of the digital asset and can do with it as they please, such as displaying it on their social media profile or selling it to someone else.</p>\r\n<br>\r\n\r\n<h2>NFT marketplaces</h2>\r\n<br>\r\n\r\n<strong>OpenSea</strong>\r\n<p>Decentralized marketplace for buying and selling NFTs, including digital art, collectibles, and virtual real estate.</p>\r\n<strong>Rarible</strong>\r\n<p>Marketplace for buying and selling NFTs, including art, music, and other digital assets.</p>\r\n<strong>SuperRare</strong>\r\n<p>Marketplace for buying and selling digital art as NFTs</p>\r\n<strong>KnownOrigin</strong>\r\n<p>Marketplace for buying and selling digital art as NFTs, with a focus on contemporary and emerging artists.</p>\r\n<strong>Foundation</strong>\r\n<p>Marketplace for buying and selling digital art as NFTs, with a focus on established artists.</p>\r\n\r\n<br>\r\n\r\n<p>These are just a few examples, and there are many other NFT marketplaces available. Some marketplaces may specialize in certain types of NFTs, such as art or collectibles, while others may offer a more general selection of NFTs. It\'s important to do your research and choose a marketplace that meets your needs and has a good reputation.</p>\r\n\r\n<br>\r\n<h2>Are NFTs cryptocurrency?</h2>\r\n<br>\r\n<p>While NFTs and cryptocurrencies share some similarities, they also have important differences. The main difference is that cryptocurrencies are fungible, meaning that one unit is interchangeable with another unit of the same type. NFTs, on the other hand, are non-fungible, meaning that each one is unique and cannot be exchanged for an equal value. For example, one Bitcoin is equal to another Bitcoin, but one NFT is not equal to another NFT. The value of an NFT is determined by market forces, such as supply and demand.</p>\r\n<br>\r\n\r\n<p>Worth noting that the value of non-fungible tokens (NFTs) can vary widely, and not all NFTs are necessarily worth a significant amount. The value of an NFT is determined by a number of factors, including the rarity and uniqueness of the item, the perceived value of the item to collectors or enthusiasts, and the overall demand for the type of NFT in question. Some NFTs may be worth a significant amount due to these factors, while others may be worth very little.</p>\r\n<p>It\'s important to do your research and consider the value of an NFT carefully before purchasing one. While it is possible to make a profit by buying and selling NFTs, it is also possible to lose money if the value of an NFT decreases. As with any investment, there are risks involved, and it\'s important to be aware of those risks and to approach the market with caution.</p>\r\n<br>', '7.webp'),
('fa-book-skull', 'Cryptojacking or Cryptomining malware', 'Malicious websites could be using your CPU to mine cryptocurrencies.', 8, 'scams', '<h2>Cryptojacking definition</h2>\r\n<br>\r\n<p>Cryptojacking is the unauthorized use of someone\'s computer to mine cryptocurrency. It occurs when a website or other online service uses a person\'s computer to mine cryptocurrency without their knowledge or consent. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Cryptomining code can run in the background on a victim\'s computer without their knowledge or consent. The victim may not be aware of the mining activity, but they may notice slower performance or delays in the execution of tasks. The cryptomining code can continue to operate while the victim uses their computer normally.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<br>\r\n<h2>How cryptojacking works</h2>\r\n<br>\r\n\r\n<li>A website or online service embeds code into their website or application that utilizes the processing power of a visitor\'s computer to mine cryptocurrency. This code can be activated as soon as the visitor loads the page or application.</li>\r\n<br>\r\n<li>The visitor\'s computer begins mining cryptocurrency in the background, while the visitor uses their computer normally. They may not be aware that their computer is being used to mine cryptocurrency.</li>\r\n<br>\r\n<li>The mined cryptocurrency is sent to the person or entity controlling the mining operation. They may use the cryptocurrency for their own purposes or sell it on an exchange.</li>\r\n<br>\r\n<li>The affected user may notice a decrease in performance or delays in the execution of tasks on their computer, but they may not realize that this is due to cryptojacking.</li>\r\n<br>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2>Here are some stelis you can take to lirotect against cryptojacking</h2>\r\n<br>\r\n<li>Use antivirus or anti-malware software that includes protection against cryptocurrency mining. These programs can detect and block cryptocurrency mining scripts and other malicious code that may be used in cryptojacking attacks.</li>\r\n<br>\r\n<li>Install a browser extension that blocks cryptocurrency mining scripts. These extensions can help prevent your computer from being used to mine cryptocurrency without your knowledge or consent.</li>\r\n<br>\r\n<li>Enable javaScript blocking in your browser. Cryptocurrency mining scripts often rely on javaScript, so disabling it can help prevent your device from being used for mining.</li>\r\n<br>\r\n<li>Be cautious when visiting unfamiliar websites. Avoid clicking on links or downloading files from untrustworthy sources, as these may contain cryptocurrency mining code.</li>\r\n<br>\r\n<li>Keep your operating system and browser up to date. Installing updates can help protect against new threats, including those that may be used in cryptojacking attacks.</li>\r\n<br>\r\n<li>Maintain browser extensions. Some attackers use malicious browser extensions or exliloit legitimate extensions to run cryptocurrency mining scripts.</li>\r\n<br>\r\n<br>\r\n<p>By following these steps, you can help protect your computer from being used for cryptocurrency mining without your knowledge or consent.</p>\r\n\r\n<br>\r\n\r\n<h2>What to do after you\'ve detected the cryptojacking and how to remove it.</h2>\r\n<br>\r\n<li>Disconnect your computer from the internet. This will prevent the cryptojacking malware from continuing to mine cryptocurrency and prevent it from communicating with the attacker\'s servers.</li>\r\n<br>\r\n<li>Run a scan with your antivirus or anti-malware software. These programs are designed to detect and remove malicious software, including cryptojacking malware. Follow the instructions provided by the software to remove the malware from your computer.</li>\r\n<br>\r\n<li>If you were using a browser extension that was compromised or used to execute the cryptojacking malware, remove the extension from your browser.</li>\r\n<br>\r\n<li>If the cryptojacking malware persists despite these steps, you may need to use a dedicated malware removal tool or seek help from a professional.</li>\r\n<br>\r\n<li>Once the cryptojacking malware has been removed, be sure to change any passwords and take other steps to secure your computer and protect against future attacks.</li>\r\n<br>\r\n<li>Reset operating system</li>\r\n<br>\r\n<p>Cryptojacking involves the unauthorized use of a person\'s computer to mine cryptocurrency, without their knowledge or consent. While the main impact of this crime is the use of the victim\'s computing power, it is important to note that this is done for the benefit of criminals who are using the power to create cryptocurrency illicitly. The victim does not receive any benefit from the mining and may suffer a decrease in performance and an increase in energy consumption on their device. It is important to take steps to protect against cryptojacking and to be aware of the risks and consequences of this crime.</p>\r\n<br>', '8.webp'),
('fa-question', 'What is Ethereum', 'Ethereum has gained significant popularity as a cryptocurrency', 9, 'whatis', '<p>Ethereum has seen widespread adoption as a cryptocurrency in recent years, with its value currently hovering around 1100.</p>\r\n<br>\r\n<p>The Ethereum network is a platform for building decentralized applications, or apps that operate on a decentralized network rather than a single centralized server. This means that no individual person or entity has control over the application. Developers can create decentralized apps using Solidity, the programming language for Ethereum. Once an app is launched on the Ethereum network, it is run on thousands of decentralized machines called nodes, which ensure that the app functions as intended. Ethereum serves as the infrastructure for running these decentralized apps on a global scale, similar to how the Bitcoin network operates.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Ethereum is often referred to as a cryptocurrency, but it is more accurately described as a decentralized platform for building and running applications. While Ethereum does have its own digital currency, called Ether, the main purpose of the Ethereum platform is to enable the creation of decentralized applications, or apps that are not controlled by any single entity. The goal of Ethereum is to decentralize the internet by allowing developers to build applications that operate on a decentralized network rather than a single centralized server. This decentralized structure can provide increased security and resilience, as well as greater transparency and accountability.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Another key feature of Ethereum is its use of a virtual machine, called the Ethereum Virtual Machine (EVM), which allows developers to build and deploy decentralized applications on the Ethereum platform. The EVM allows developers to write code in various programming languages, making it more accessible than other blockchain platforms that require developers to learn a proprietary language.</p>\r\n<br>\r\n\r\n<h2>In terms of its use as a digital currency, Ethereum has a number of advantages over other cryptocurrencies:</h2>\r\n<br>\r\n<br>\r\n<li>Smart contracts: Ethereum enables the creation of smart contracts, which are self-executing contracts with the terms of the agreement between buyer and seller written directly into lines of code. These contracts can be used to automate a wide range of transactions and processes, making them more efficient and transparent.</li>\r\n<br>\r\n<li>Decentralized application platform: Ethereum is a decentralized platform for building and running applications, or dApps. This allows developers to create a wide range of decentralized applications that operate on a decentralized network rather than a single centralized server.</li>\r\n<br>\r\n<li>Wide programming language support: Ethereum\'s Virtual Machine (EVM) allows developers to write code in various programming languages, making it more accessible than other blockchain platforms that require developers to learn a proprietary language.</li>\r\n<br>\r\n<li>Fast transaction speeds: Ethereum has faster transaction speeds than many other cryptocurrencies, which makes it well-suited for applications that require fast and secure transactions.</li>\r\n<br>\r\n<li>Low fees: Ethereum has lower fees compared to many other cryptocurrencies, which makes it more cost-effective for applications that require frequent transactions.</li>\r\n<br>\r\n<li>Large developer community: Ethereum has a large and active developer community, which has helped it to attract a wide range of applications and use cases.</li>\r\n<br>\r\n<li>Active development ecosystem: Ethereum has an active development ecosystem, with regular updates and improvements to the platform. This helps to ensure that it remains relevant and well-suited to the needs of developers and users.</li>\r\n<br>\r\n\r\n<h2>Potential disadvantages of Ethereum:</h2>\r\n<br>\r\n\r\n<li>Scalability issues: Potential drawback of Ethereum is that its decentralized structure can make it challenging to handle a large volume of transactions, leading to slower speeds and higher fees for users. This is due to the decentralized nature of the platform, which can make it more difficult to scale and accommodate a large number of transactions.</li>\r\n<br>\r\n<li>Complexity: Ethereum is a more complex platform than some other cryptocurrencies, which can make it more difficult for new users to understand and use.</li>\r\n<br>\r\n<li>Lack of interoperability: Ethereum is its own independent platform, which means that it does not have built-in interoperability with other blockchain platforms. This can make it more difficult to use Ethereum in conjunction with other platforms or to transfer assets between platforms.</li>\r\n<br>\r\n<li>Regulation: Cryptocurrencies, including Ethereum, are often subject to regulatory uncertainty, which can create risks for investors and users.</li>\r\n<br>\r\n<li>Security vulnerabilities: Like any digital platform, Ethereum is vulnerable to security breaches and attacks. This can create risks for users and developers who rely on the platform.</li>\r\n<br>\r\n<li>Dependence on external factors: The demand for Ethereum can be influenced by investor sentiment, which can fluctuate based on a variety of factors. The regulatory environment for cryptocurrencies, including Ethereum, can impact their value and stability. Ethereum\'s value and stability can also be affected by broader market conditions, such as the overall state of the economy and investor confidence.</li>\r\n<br>\r\n<br>\r\n\r\n<p>Important to keep in mind that investing in Ethereum carries significant risks, including the possibility of losing all or part of your investment. It is important to carefully consider these risks before making any investment decisions.</p>\r\n<br>\r\n<p>Source: Trust me bro</p>\r\n<br>', '9.webp');

